Dan,

Nothing wrong with an occasional to the floor get going move----

But holding it there is sydasue---

I try to keep my 74 at no more than 3800---4000--rpm for any length of
time---

I learned the hard way-----burnt #3 valve trying to hold it at 75 on
I-90 for about 6--7 hours---

I don't have any inclination of doing the heads again---

PHOOEY---!!

65--70 seems to be an acceptable speed to cruise at for any length of
time---

Live and learn---

Later,

Terry

 
