I also am the new owner of a 1971 Westy, as you may know by now, and the
PO also fully rebuilt the engine. It is entirely stock as well, no
guages or tach. I used to own a 75 Transporter with a 79 engine in it
which felt like a Hemi-Cuda compared to my new '71!!! 
I was also wondering about acceptable speeds and engine life - 55-60 mph
max feels like a reasonable cruise on the highway, and that's fine - no
problem - I'm used to going slow on my aircooled BMW motorcycle - but
what about city driving? Should I be _never_ using full throttle? It
seems like I have serious trouble getting rolling if I don't goose it a
little bit in first or second. 
My second question is about the warmup procedure - the motor seems
veeerrry unhappy when cold - I definitely can't start it up and drive
away like I used to in my '79 - what is the normal procedure for warming
up the engine before driving away? 
